          <p>
            The Yellow Sea between China and Korea is the single most important refuelling stop
            in the East Asian–Australasian Flyway — the flyway our kuaka use. Millions of
            shorebirds <em>must</em> stop here to feed on invertebrates in vast intertidal
            mudflats before continuing to their Arctic breeding grounds.
          </p>

          <p>
            Land reclamation — converting mudflats into farmland, aquaculture ponds, and industrial
            zones — has destroyed <strong>35.6%</strong> of the Yellow Sea's tidal flats. In the
            Yellow River Delta alone, shorebird numbers have dropped by <strong>90%</strong>
            between 1995 and 2020.
          </p>

