          <!-- Dams and Longfin Eel -->
          <h4>Dams Blocking Fish Migration — NZ's Longfin Eel</h4>

          <p>
            The longfin eel (<em>Anguilla dieffenbachii</em>, tuna) is endemic to New Zealand
            and undertakes one of the most remarkable migrations of any animal. After spending
            <strong>60–80+ years</strong> growing in freshwater, mature females migrate thousands
            of kilometres to spawn somewhere in the deep Pacific tropics — then die. The larvae
            drift back on ocean currents, eventually finding New Zealand rivers and climbing
            upstream as tiny glass eels.
          </p>

          <!-- Dam Barrier SVG -->
          <div class="dam-diagram fade-in-up">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 700 280" class="dam-svg" aria-label="Dam blocking eel migration diagram">
