          <h3 id="other-threats">Other Human Threats to Migrants</h3>

          <div class="section-header-with-audio">
            <h4>A Web of Pressures</h4>
            <button class="audio-btn" id="other-threats-audio" title="Listen to Dr Eliot explain this">&#9654;</button>
          </div>

          <p>
            Climate change, habitat loss and light pollution are the biggest threats — but
            migratory species face a web of additional human-caused pressures:
          </p>

          <div class="threats-grid fade-in-up">
            <div class="threat-card">
              <div class="threat-card__icon">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" width="40" height="40"><circle cx="24" cy="24" r="18" fill="none" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M24,6 L24,42 M24,6 L30,18 L24,14 L18,18 Z" fill="var(--fluoro-cyan)" opacity="0.3" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="1"/><path d="M14,16 L34,32 M34,16 L14,32" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.5"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h5 class="threat-card__title">Wind Turbines</h5>
              <p class="threat-card__text">
                Kill 0.6–1.5 million birds and 1.7–2.8 million bats per year in the US alone.
                Bats often die from <strong>barotrauma</strong> — internal haemorrhage from rapid
                pressure changes near blade tips, even without direct contact.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="threat-card">
              <div class="threat-card__icon">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" width="40" height="40"><rect x="10" y="8" width="28" height="32" fill="none" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="1.5" rx="2"/><rect x="15" y="13" width="8" height="8" fill="rgba(125,249,255,0.2)" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="0.8"/><rect x="25" y="13" width="8" height="8" fill="rgba(125,249,255,0.2)" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="0.8"/><rect x="15" y="23" width="8" height="8" fill="rgba(125,249,255,0.2)" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="0.8"/><rect x="25" y="23" width="8" height="8" fill="rgba(125,249,255,0.2)" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="0.8"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h5 class="threat-card__title">Glass Buildings</h5>
              <p class="threat-card__text">
                Up to <strong>1 billion bird deaths per year</strong> in the US from building
                collisions. Glass is invisible — birds see reflected sky or a through-view and
                fly straight into it.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="threat-card">
              <div class="threat-card__icon">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" width="40" height="40"><path d="M10,38 Q15,30 20,32 Q25,20 30,28 Q35,22 38,30 L38,38 Z" fill="rgba(125,249,255,0.15)" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M18,38 L18,42 M30,38 L30,42" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="1"/><circle cx="24" cy="15" r="4" fill="none" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="2 2"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h5 class="threat-card__title">Overfishing</h5>
              <p class="threat-card__text">
                Industrial fishing depletes the forage fish (anchovies, sardines, krill) that
                marine migrants depend on. Tītī travelling to the North Pacific find less food.
                Longline bycatch kills hundreds of thousands of seabirds annually.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="threat-card">
              <div class="threat-card__icon">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" width="40" height="40"><circle cx="24" cy="20" r="8" fill="none" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M24,28 L24,40 M18,42 L30,42" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M20,16 L28,24 M28,16 L20,24" stroke="var(--fluoro-pink)" stroke-width="1.5"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h5 class="threat-card__title">Pesticides</h5>
              <p class="threat-card__text">
                <strong>Neonicotinoids</strong> — systemic insecticides absorbed into all plant
                tissues including nectar — are the strongest predictor of monarch butterfly
                decline. Milkweed habitat loss from herbicide-resistant crops compounds the problem.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="threat-card">
              <div class="threat-card__icon">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" width="40" height="40"><path d="M8,35 Q15,30 24,32 Q33,30 40,35" fill="none" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M12,30 Q18,25 24,27 Q30,25 36,30" fill="none" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.5"/><path d="M20,18 Q24,12 28,18" fill="none" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="1.5"/><circle cx="24" cy="14" r="3" fill="rgba(125,249,255,0.2)" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="1"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h5 class="threat-card__title">Shipping Noise</h5>
              <p class="threat-card__text">
                Ocean background noise has increased <strong>16-fold</strong> since the 1960s.
                Humpback whales alter migration routes, reduce communication, and show chronic
                stress responses. Military sonar causes mass strandings in beaked whales.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="threat-card">
              <div class="threat-card__icon">
                <svg viewBox="0 0 48 48" width="40" height="40"><path d="M16,38 Q16,28 24,24 Q32,28 32,38" fill="none" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="1.5"/><circle cx="24" cy="18" r="5" fill="none" stroke="var(--fluoro-cyan)" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M20,14 L18,10 M28,14 L30,10 M24,13 L24,8" stroke="var(--fluoro-pink)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h5 class="threat-card__title">Invasive Predators</h5>
              <p class="threat-card__text">
                Rats, stoats, and cats devastate ground-nesting migratory species at breeding
                colonies. Tītī returning to nest on NZ offshore islands face intense predator
                pressure — one of the most acute threats to island-breeding seabirds worldwide.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>


