                temperature) from hatching. The birds still showed annual cycles of fat
                deposition and migratory restlessness, but these cycles were approximately
                10–11 months long rather than exactly 12 months.
                <br><br>
                (a) Explain what these results demonstrate about the control of migration timing.
                <br>
                (b) Explain the role of photoperiod in the context of these results.
                <br>
                (c) Discuss the adaptive advantage of having both an endogenous clock and an
                external Zeitgeber, rather than relying on only one system.
              </p>
              <textarea class="answer-input answer-input--xl" data-answer="6" placeholder="Write your answer here..."></textarea>
